<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Alexa Demo</title>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
	<meta name="description" content="A Basecamp dashboard, built with node.">
	<meta name="author" content="@That_Drew_Guy">
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.4/css/bootstrap.min.css"/>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.5.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/stylesheets/main.css"/>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.4/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery-dateFormat/1.0/jquery.dateFormat.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
	<nav class="navbar navbar-default navbar-static-top navbar-inverse">
		<div class="container">
			<ul class="nav navbar-nav">
				<li class="active">
					<a href="/"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-home"></span> Home</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</nav>
	<div class="jumbotron text-center">
		<div class="container">
			<a href="/" class="lang-logo">
				<img src="/lang-logo.png">
			</a>
			<h1>Welcome to the Walgreens skill</h1>
			<p>Alexa Skills Kit (ASK) is a JSON based language for the Amazon Echo. This POC is written for node.JS and handles the multitude of requests that ASK will send over.</p>
			<a type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" href="/schema"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-th-list"></span> Basic Schema</a>
			<a type="button" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" href="/utterances"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-equalizer"></span> Sample Utterances</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-12 text-center">
				<div class="well">
					<h2>Demo video:</h2>
					<div align="center">
					    <a href="https://db.tt/Rc58jWyT" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary">Watch here!</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-12 text-center">
				<div class="well">
					<h2>Alexa, Start Walgreens.</h2>
					This request starts the skill or "conversation". Response is a simple introduction and a wait for the user to ask something.
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-3 text-center">
				<div class="well">
					<h4>What is the nearest store?</h4>
					<hr/>
					Returns the nearest store for the user, can read their preferred location as well. This would hopefully also read store hours at some point.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-3 text-center">
				<div class="well">
					<h4>What is my Balance Rewards total?</h4>
					<hr/>
					Returns the total balance rewards points for a user, as well the amount they need to get to the next savings bracket.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-3 text-center">
				<div class="well">
					<h4>Find the status of my current refill.</h4>
					<hr/>
					Returns the status of the current refills. This is one that still needs some work, but it could grow into a very indepth conversation with our IC+ systems.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-3 text-center">
				<div class="well">
					<h4>Help me! or Thank you.</h4>
					<hr/>
					Basic 'help me' with what to say, and thank you text initiating the exit or end of conversation response.
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<hr>
	</div>
	<div class="container">
		<div class="alert alert-info text-center" role="alert">
			Any ideas? Send me an message at: <a href="mailto:apidrew@walgreens.com" class="alert-link"><span class="fa fa-envelope"></span> apidrew@walgreens.com</a>.
		</div>
		<hr>
	</div>
</body>
</html>


